ar as per regulatory norms.</td></tr><tr data-start="1173" data-end="1472"><td data-start="1173" data-end="1209" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1175" data-end="1208">Plumbing, Sanitation, &amp; Water</strong></td><td data-start="1209" data-end="1472" data-col-size="xl">Dual water supply lines (domestic &amp; treated water for flushing/landscaping). Proper plumbing lines extended to each plot. Wastewater and sewage treated through STP. Rainwater harvesting and recharge pits provided. Adequate sump and overhead tanks for storage.</td></tr><tr data-start="1473" data-end="1718"><td data-start="1473" data-end="1504" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1475" data-end="1503">Finishing / Common Areas</strong></td><td data-start="1504" data-end="1718" data-col-size="xl">Lush landscaping in common zones with avenue plantation. Low-maintenance plants used throughout. Street furnishings and lighting provided. Premium entrance gateway and boundary treatment for community identity.</td></tr><tr data-start="1719" data-end="1979"><td data-start="1719" data-end="1743" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1721" data-end="1742">Safety &amp; Security</strong></td><td data-start="1743" data-end="1979" data-col-size="xl">Gated entry with a security cabin. 24/7 security personnel with controlled access. RFID / boom-barriers at main gates. CCTV surveillance at critical points including entrance, exit, and play areas. Visitor vehicle management system.</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>',
